content.text: Predicting whether artificial general intelligence (AGI) will be achieved by 2030 is uncertain. While significant progress is being made in AI research, many experts believe AGI—AI with human-like understanding and reasoning—may take longer due to the complexity of replicating general intelligence. Some are optimistic about breakthroughs within this decade, but consensus leans toward a timeline beyond 2030.
